cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the asymptotic analysis of coding schemes for source coding and rate distortion problems. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses complexity tradeoffs in the context of rate distortion problems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a layered code construction for reducing complexity in point-to-point lossy compression problems. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper may have applications in network coding and distributed source coding. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with source coding and rate distortion problems, which are relevant in multimedia applications.
